article.headline: North Florida 72, Kennesaw 68
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Alain Laroche scored 23 points and grabbed 14 rebounds to lead North Florida to a 72-68 victory over Kennesaw State on Friday. Rashad Williams scored 17 points and had 11 rebounds for North Florida (6-15, 3-11 Atlantic Sun). Chris Timberlake scored 15 points for North Florida, which got 10 from Ryan Daugherty. Laroche had back-to-back layups in the final minute to help spark a game-ending 8-0 run by the Ospreys, who were down 68-64 after Andre Morgan hit a pair of free throws for Kennesaw State with 1:25 left. Morgan led all scorers with 35 points, and Brent Ragsdale added 13 for the Owls (11-12, 9-5).
